protected_spaces_details.description: Provision for children and young people

description: Non-material amendment to planning permission dated 19/07/2018 ref 2017/4380 (Erection of a podium building with three buildings above (providing part 2, 6, 8, 11 and 24 storeys plus basement level) to provide 299 residential units including affordable and market housing, with circa 5,943 sq m of Class D1 education space, including 537 sq m of associated Class A3/A4 caf and drinking establishment space. Provision of car parking, cycle parking, refuse storage and plant in the basement, and associated roof plant enclosure. Removal of and replacement of trees, landscaping, provision of and improvements to public realm including the removal of tree planters, widening of street frontages and resurfacing of York Place (on north-western side) to create a shared surface and introduction of a drop off point)   Proposed non-material amendments are:  Changes to configuration of RAD accommodation on ground and first floors Change from 2 bed 4 person units to 2 bed 3 person units in Blocks A, B and C (47 units) Change from 1 bed 2 person intermediate units to 1 bed 1 person intermediate units in Block A (3 units)  Internalisation of amenity space to four flats in Block C on 12th and 13th floors Change of material to frame of Block C from GRC to PPC metal cladding  Installation of metal bars to glazed balcony balustrades on all levels (Block C).  Changes to number and positions of windows, balconies and glazed doors on both side elevations (facing Block A and Block B)  Installation of new (matching) windows in rear elevation (Block C) on 16th and 17th floors Change the aluminium windows to composite aluminium/timber windows (Blocks A, B and C)  Provision of metal balustrades to all balconies on Blocks A and B  Change horizontal and vertical tracery (i.e banding) from GRC to aluminium (Blocks A and B)  Increase the fascia depth of all balcony fascias from 300mm to 365mm. Reduction in height of plant enclosures on roofs (Blocks A and B). Change to windows/doors at ground floor level side elevation Blocks A and B White bricks now proposed for side elevations of Blocks A and B (facing Block C)  Installation of new (recessed) glazed doors to first floor flats (Block B rear elevation)
